      <amcr:chranene_udaje>
        <amcr:nazev>Praha-Jinonice - fence 1 - Butovice (In the playgrounds, In the playgrounds)</amcr:nazev>
        <amcr:popis>Location On the playgrounds, sometimes also On the playgrounds. A distinctive spur shaped by the Prokop and Dalai Streams. The site is now understood to be a two-piece; the location of Behind St Lawrence has not yet been established. Two patchy strips of cross-fencing of the spur (the fortification of the acropolis today in the form of a substantial terrace and the fortification of the foreshore in the form of a low wall). A little research (on the S side) in the 1960s showed the perimeter fortifications of the acropolis. Strong settlement of the primeval (primarily the Vivian culture), as well as early medieval (old-castle-center, with the fortifications having stone elements indicating a rather younger date within this interval). Early medieval settlement ends just before the turn of the 9th and 10th centuries.</amcr:popis>
      </amcr:chranene_udaje>
    </amcr:lokalita>
